OL,3,CInfected blood scandal victim says he
OL,4,Cis 'worth more financially if he died'
OL,6,FThe inquiry into the biggest treatment
OL,7,Fdisaster in the NHS concluded that the
OL,8,Fscandal "could largely have been
OL,9,Favoided" and there was a "pervasive"
OL,10,Fcover-up to hide the truth.
OL,12,FIt found deliberate attempts were made
OL,13,Fto conceal the disaster, including
OL,14,Fevidence of Whitehall officials
OL,15,Fdestroying documents.
OL,17,FMore than 30,000 people were infected
OL,18,Fwith deadly viruses while they were
OL,19,Freceiving NHS care between the 1970s
OL,20,Fand 1990s.
